# Truegrynd – Coding Guidelines

## TypeScript
- Use TypeScript everywhere — no `.js` files in `src/`
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for data shapes; use `interface` for extension/implementation
- Avoid `any` — use `unknown` with type guards when needed
- Always type function return values explicitly for exported functions

## File & Function Size Limits
- Max 200 lines per component file
- Max 50 lines per function
- Max 3 levels of nesting
- Max 4 parameters per function (use options object otherwise)

## React Patterns
- Functional components only — no class components
- Extract all logic into custom hooks; components handle rendering only
- No inline object/array literals as JSX props (causes unnecessary re-renders)
- Use early returns to avoid deep nesting
- `const` by default — never `let` unless mutation is needed

## Naming Conventions
| Item | Convention | Example |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Component | PascalCase | `ChallengeCard` |
| Hook | camelCase prefixed `use` | `useLeaderboard` |
| Service function | camelCase | `submitScore` |
| Type/Interface | PascalCase | `Score`, `Profile` |
| Constant | SCREAMING_SNAKE | `TOP_10_THRESHOLD` |
| CSS class | kebab-case via Tailwind | — |

## Imports
Order: React → third-party → internal (lib, features, components) → types → styles

## No Production Logs
- Never commit `console.log` — use a logger utility if needed
- No debug artifacts in production code

## Comments
- Only explain non-obvious intent or trade-offs
- Never narrate what the code does (no `// increment counter`)
